# """
# train_model.py
# ===============

# This script trains a lightweight U‑Net segmentation model to identify HI shells
# in moment maps.  It is designed to run efficiently on CPU‑only hardware such as
# an Apple M1 with limited memory.  Training and inference operate on tiles
# generated by ``data_processing.py``; each tile contains an intensity map and
# corresponding binary mask.

# Key features:

# * A simplified U‑Net architecture with three encoder–decoder stages and
#   reduced channel counts (default base number of filters is 32).  This
#   drastically reduces parameter count compared with standard U‑Nets while
#   retaining the skip connections necessary to capture multi‑scale context.
# * Combination of binary cross‑entropy (BCE) and Dice loss to balance
#   pixel‑wise classification and overlap metrics.  Dice loss mitigates
#   class‑imbalance by focusing on the relative intersection between predicted
#   and true masks.
# * Dataset class that reads NumPy ``.npz`` files generated by
#   ``data_processing.py``.  It normalizes the image values by subtracting the
#   median and dividing by the interquartile range (robust to outliers).
# * Training loop with progress logging, basic metric computation (precision,
#   recall, F1), and optional early stopping.

# Example usage:

#     python train_model.py --data_dir data/patches --epochs 25 --batch_size 4

# This will train the model and save the best performing weights (by Dice
# coefficient) to ``model_best.pth`` in the working directory.
# """

